<paragraph blockId="3.[956,1312,1458,1485]" box="[956,1312,1458,1485]" pageId="3" pageNumber="12">
<heading box="[956,1312,1458,1485]" centered="true" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="3" pageNumber="12" reason="3">
9. 
<taxonomicName authority="A. Braun" box="[984,1312,1458,1485]" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Selaginellales" pageId="3" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="homaliae">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[984,1207,1458,1485]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="12">Selaginella homaliae</emphasis>
A. Braun
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[835,1456,1516,1540]" pageId="3" pageNumber="12" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="3.[811,1457,1516,2028]" box="[835,1456,1516,1540]" pageId="3" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis box="[835,1228,1516,1540]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="12">Annales des Sciences Naturelles, Botanique</emphasis>
, série 5, 3: 274 (1865).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="13" pageId="3" pageNumber="12" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[811,1457,1516,2028]" pageId="3" pageNumber="12">
Dans le protologue il est noté: « tertiam his affinem, cui nomen 
<taxonomicName box="[811,933,1586,1613]" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Selaginellales" pageId="3" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="homaliae">
<emphasis box="[811,933,1586,1613]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="12">S. homaliae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
propter similitudinem quandam cum Homalia trichomanoide imposui, cl. R. Spruce prope Panure, ad Rio Uaupes legit. (n°2534)».
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[811,1457,1516,2028]" pageId="3" pageNumber="12">
Braun effectue seulement une comparaison avec d’autres taxons, sans donner à 
<taxonomicName box="[1043,1163,1714,1740]" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Selaginellales" pageId="3" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="homaliae">
<emphasis box="[1043,1163,1714,1740]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="12">S. homaliae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
de description comportant un caractère propre qui le différencie des autres espèces. C’est ainsi que 
<bibRefCitation author="Reed" box="[909,1033,1778,1805]" firstAuthor="Reed" pageId="3" pageNumber="12" pagination="1 - 287" refId="ref6019" refString="REED C. F. 1965 - 1966. - Index Selaginellarum. Memorias da Sociedade Broteriana ser. 2, 18: 1 - 287." type="journal article" year="1965">Reed (1965</bibRefCitation>
-1966) considère la notation d’A. 
<bibRefCitation author="Braun" firstAuthor="Braun" pageId="3" pageNumber="12" pagination="270 - 311" refId="ref5208" refString="BRAUN A. 1865. - Prodromus Florae Novo-Granatensis, in PLANCHON J. E. (ed.), Annales des Sciences naturelles, Botanique, serie 5, 3: 270 - 311." type="journal article" year="1865">Braun (1865)</bibRefCitation>
comme non valide, l’indiquant ‘ 
<emphasis box="[1240,1383,1810,1836]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="12">nom. subnud.</emphasis>
’.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[811,1457,1516,2028]" pageId="3" pageNumber="12">
C’est 
<bibRefCitation author="BAKER J. G." box="[897,1033,1841,1868]" firstAuthor="Baker" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Botany" pageId="3" pageNumber="12" pagination="210 - 213" part="21" refId="ref5093" refString="BAKER J. G. 1883. - A synopsis of the genus Selaginella. Journal of Botany 21: 210 - 213, 332 - 336." title="A synopsis of the genus Selaginella" type="journal article" year="1883">Baker (1883</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Baker" box="[1044,1101,1842,1868]" firstAuthor="Baker" pageId="3" pageNumber="12" pagination="1 - 159" refId="ref5121" refString="BAKER J. G. 1887. - Handbook of the Fern-Allies. A synopsis of the genera and species of the natural orders - Equisetaceae, Lycopodiaceae, Selaginellaceae, Rhizocarpae. Fern Allies 53: 1 - 159." type="journal article" year="1887">1887</bibRefCitation>
) qui effectue la description de ce taxon (
<taxonomicName authority="A. Braun" authorityName="A. Braun" box="[890,1214,1873,1900]" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Selaginellales" pageId="3" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="homaliae">
<emphasis box="[890,1103,1873,1899]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="12">Selaginella homaliae</emphasis>
A. Braun
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis box="[1229,1251,1874,1899]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="12">in</emphasis>
Crypt. 
<emphasis box="[1337,1448,1874,1900]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="12">New Gran</emphasis>
. 352; 
<emphasis box="[869,891,1906,1931]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="12">in</emphasis>
Baker, 
<emphasis box="[972,1160,1905,1931]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="12">Journal of Botanic</emphasis>
21: 212 [1883]; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="12">Handbook of the Fern Allies</emphasis>
53 [n° 76] [1887]). Mais il y est noté: «Hab. Cataracts of Jaruma and Panuré, Upper Amazon, Spruce 2534!, 2941!, Traill 1437!».
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[130,776,215,883]" pageId="4" pageNumber="13">
<bibRefCitation author="ALSTON A. H. G. &amp; JERMY A. C. &amp; RANKIN J. M." box="[155,362,215,242]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Alston" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History), Botany" pageId="4" pageNumber="13" pagination="233 - 330" part="9" refId="ref5018" refString="ALSTON A. H. G., JERMY A. C. &amp; RANKIN J. M. 1981. - The genus Selaginella in tropical South America. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History), Botany 9 (4): 233 - 330" title="The genus Selaginella in tropical South America" type="journal article" year="1981">
Alston 
<emphasis box="[232,275,215,241]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="13">et al</emphasis>
. (1981)
</bibRefCitation>
citent les trois spécimens (indiqués cidessus) comme des 
<typeStatus box="[343,438,248,274]" pageId="4" pageNumber="13">syntypes</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[130,776,215,883]" pageId="4" pageNumber="13">
<bibRefCitation author="Valdespino" box="[155,341,279,306]" firstAuthor="Valdespino" pageId="4" pageNumber="13" refId="ref6146" refString="VALDESPINO QUINTERRO I. A. 1995. - A Monographic Revision of Selaginella P. Beauv. Subgenus Heterostachys Baker in Central and South America. Degree of Doctor of Philosophy, The City University of New York, 405 p." type="book" year="1995">
Valdespino (
<quantity box="[285,341,279,306]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0673" pageId="4" pageNumber="13" unit="in" value="1995.0">1995</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
<emphasis box="[344,415,279,305]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="13">in herb</emphasis>
.) désigne le spécimen 
<emphasis box="[646,773,279,305]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="13">Spruce 2534</emphasis>
déposé à B comme l’holotype et les spécimens de K comme des isotypes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[130,776,215,883]" pageId="4" pageNumber="13">
En définitive, nous suivons Valdespino pour typifier ce taxon avec un spécimen de 
<emphasis box="[435,566,407,433]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="13">Spruce 2534</emphasis>
, car en conformité avec le protologue. Cependant, nous avons constaté que, sous ce numéro, étaient regroupées des récoltes effectuées à deux endroits différents.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
